docs.abstract: The president will cast himself as a friend to farmers in a speech on Monday, but his position on trade and some parts of the new tax law threaten to undercut their interests.
docs.snippet: The president will cast himself as a friend to farmers in a speech on Monday, but his position on trade and some parts of the new tax law threaten to undercut their interests.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump will head to Tennessee on Monday to appeal to farmers, a key demographic that helped elect him, as he promotes his tax law and previews a new White House strategy to help rural America.

headline.main: As Trump Appeals to Farmers, Some of His Policies Don’t
headline.print_headline: As Trump Appeals to Farmers, Some of the Policies He’s Pursuing Don’t

docs.abstract: Many once-great towns in America have lost their luster. If a philanthropist wants to help turn one around, the complex challenges call for a community-based focus.

docs.lead_paragraph: Darla Moore came from humble roots. She grew up in Lake City, S.C., an agricultural community with a population of 6,675.

headline.main: When Your Fixer-Upper Is Your Hometown
headline.print_headline: Investing in Your Hometown Is About Investing Yourself

docs.abstract: In an unusually public spat, Amazon is rethinking some building projects in Seattle because of a new tax being considered by the City Council.
docs.snippet: In an unusually public spat, Amazon is rethinking some building projects in Seattle because of a new tax being considered by the City Council.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Amazon abruptly escalated a fight with its hometown on Wednesday, halting major expansion plans in Seattle because of a tax being considered by the City Council.

headline.main: Amazon Pauses Huge Development Plans in Seattle Over Tax Plan
headline.print_headline: Amazon Halts Building Plan Over Tax Spat

docs.abstract: After Amazon’s bold threat to curtail development in its hometown, the Seattle City Council approved a smaller tax than originally envisioned. Amazon says it’s still “apprehensive” about the future.
docs.snippet: After Amazon’s bold threat to curtail development in its hometown, the Seattle City Council approved a smaller tax than originally envisioned. Amazon says it’s still “apprehensive” about the future.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — After intense lobbying by local businesses and a bold threat by Amazon to curtail development in its hometown, the Seattle City Council on Monday approved a smaller and more limited tax on big companies than originally envisioned.

headline.main: Seattle Scales Back Tax in Face of Amazon’s Revolt, but Tensions Linger
headline.print_headline: Seattle Scales Back Big-Business Tax in Face of Revolt by Amazon

docs.abstract: The company also said it would raise the price of its popular Prime membership service to $119 from $99.

docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Jeff Bezos, Amazon’s founder and chief executive, long ago figured out how to keep Amazon’s sales figures shooting skyward. Now he is doing the same with profit.

headline.main: Amazon’s Profit Swells to $1.6 Billion, Lifted by Its Cloud Business
headline.print_headline: Amazon Profits Swell to $1.6 Billion With Rise of Its Business Services
